    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-01T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="200"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/313: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-01T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 1, 1932—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 2—2:45 a.m.<note n="17" xml:id="d200fn17">Telegram in
                            two sections.</note>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>883. [Paragraphs 1 through 4 of this telegram summarize material printed in the
                    Minister’s despatch No. 1656, August 2, 1932, with enclosure of epitomized
                    record of statements made by <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_UCY1">Count
                        Uchida</persName>, printed in <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_95">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, volume I, pages
                        95</ref>–<ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_98">98</ref>.]</p>
                <p>5. The above sounds to me like a well-thought-out statement of policy which the
                    present Japanese Government is prepared to defend by force of arms and an
                    interpretation of the application of the League Covenant, the Nine-Power Treaty
                    and the Kellogg Pact to situations of the kind that has been created by Japanese
                    initiative in Manchuria which will bear consideration.</p>
                <p>Tokyo informed by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
